{
  "page": "Robb Stark's battle guard",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Nicholas_GregoryRobbStark.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/3/3a/Nicholas_GregoryRobbStark.jpg/300px-Nicholas_GregoryRobbStark.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"266\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/3/3a/Nicholas_GregoryRobbStark.jpg/450px-Nicholas_GregoryRobbStark.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/3/3a/Nicholas_GregoryRobbStark.jpg/600px-Nicholas_GregoryRobbStark.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Nicholas_GregoryRobbStark.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a href=\"/index.php/Robb_Stark\" title=\"Robb Stark\">Robb Stark</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/King_in_the_North\" title=\"King in the North\">King in the North</a>, by Nicholas Gregory © Fantasy Flight Games</div></div></div>\n<p><b>Robb Stark's battle guard</b> are a group of highborn protectors of <a href=\"/index.php/Robb_Stark\" title=\"Robb Stark\">Robb Stark</a>, the heir of Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Eddard_Stark\" title=\"Eddard Stark\">Eddard Stark</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Winterfell\" title=\"Winterfell\">Winterfell</a>. Unlike the <a href=\"/index.php/Kingsguard\" title=\"Kingsguard\">Kingsguard</a>, this is not an official order with any sworn vows, but an informal group of battle companions.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot63.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot63.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Recent_Events\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Recent Events</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#A_Game_of_Thrones\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Game of Thrones</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#A_Clash_of_Kings\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Clash of Kings</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#A_Storm_of_Swords\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Storm of Swords</i></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Known_Members\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Known Members</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_Events\">Recent Events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Robb_Stark%27s_battle_guard&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent Events\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Game_of_Thrones\"><i>A Game of Thrones</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Robb_Stark%27s_battle_guard&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Game of Thrones\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Chris_Rahn_The_Battle_of_the_Whispering_WoodII.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/f/f3/Chris_Rahn_The_Battle_of_the_Whispering_WoodII.png/300px-Chris_Rahn_The_Battle_of_the_Whispering_WoodII.png\" width=\"300\" height=\"195\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/f/f3/Chris_Rahn_The_Battle_of_the_Whispering_WoodII.png/450px-Chris_Rahn_The_Battle_of_the_Whispering_WoodII.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/f/f3/Chris_Rahn_The_Battle_of_the_Whispering_WoodII.png/600px-Chris_Rahn_The_Battle_of_the_Whispering_WoodII.png 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Chris_Rahn_The_Battle_of_the_Whispering_WoodII.png\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Jaime_Lannister\" title=\"Jaime Lannister\">Jaime Lannister</a> is captured in the <a href=\"/index.php/Battle_in_the_Whispering_Wood\" title=\"Battle in the Whispering Wood\">Whispering Wood</a>, by Chris Rahn © Fantasy Flight Games</div></div></div>\n<p>When <a href=\"/index.php/Robb_Stark\" title=\"Robb Stark\">Robb Stark</a> rides to war against the <a href=\"/index.php/House_Lannister\" title=\"House Lannister\">Lannisters</a> after <a href=\"/index.php/Arrest_of_Eddard_Stark\" title=\"Arrest of Eddard Stark\">the arrest</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a> of his father, Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Eddard_Stark\" title=\"Eddard Stark\">Eddard Stark</a>, he surrounds himself with highborn warriors. Just as he rides with a different lord at the head of his army every day in order to know and honor his bannermen, Robb's choice of bodyguards serves to honor the houses from which they are picked. Most of these fighters are young men, although <a href=\"/index.php/Dacey_Mormont\" title=\"Dacey Mormont\">Dacey Mormont</a> is female and Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Wendel_Manderly\" title=\"Wendel Manderly\">Wendel Manderly</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Robin_Flint\" title=\"Robin Flint\">Robin Flint</a> are mature men.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot63.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot63.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Forming Robb's battle guard during the <a href=\"/index.php/Battle_in_the_Whispering_Wood\" title=\"Battle in the Whispering Wood\">battle in the Whispering Wood</a> are thirty nobles.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot63.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot63.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> Before being captured in the battle, Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Jaime_Lannister\" title=\"Jaime Lannister\">Jaime Lannister</a> slays <a href=\"/index.php/Torrhen_Karstark\" title=\"Torrhen Karstark\">Torrhen Karstark</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Eddard_Karstark\" title=\"Eddard Karstark\">Eddard Karstark</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/Daryn_Hornwood\" title=\"Daryn Hornwood\">Daryn Hornwood</a> while fighting to get to Robb.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot63.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot63.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Robb relieves <a href=\"/index.php/Riverrun\" title=\"Riverrun\">Riverrun</a> in the <a href=\"/index.php/Battle_of_the_Camps\" title=\"Battle of the Camps\">Battle of the Camps</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot69.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot69.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> After Eddard's execution by order of King <a href=\"/index.php/Joffrey_Baratheon\" title=\"Joffrey Baratheon\">Joffrey I Baratheon</a>, Robb is proclaimed <a href=\"/index.php/King_in_the_North\" title=\"King in the North\">King in the North</a> in the <a href=\"/index.php/Great_Hall_of_Riverrun\" title=\"Great Hall of Riverrun\">Great Hall of Riverrun</a> by <a href=\"/index.php/North\" title=\"North\">northern</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Riverlands\" title=\"Riverlands\">river</a> lords.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot71.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot71.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Clash_of_Kings\"><i>A Clash of Kings</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Robb_Stark%27s_battle_guard&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Clash of Kings\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Robb's companions continue to fight bravely during his invasion of the <a href=\"/index.php/Westerlands\" title=\"Westerlands\">westerlands</a> and to serve him in other critical capacities. Robb sends northmen and rivermen to protect his mother, <a href=\"/index.php/Catelyn_Stark\" title=\"Catelyn Stark\">Catelyn Stark</a>, during her journey to treat with <a href=\"/index.php/Renly_Baratheon\" title=\"Renly Baratheon\">Renly Baratheon</a> at <a href=\"/index.php/Bitterbridge\" title=\"Bitterbridge\">Bitterbridge</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Stannis_Baratheon\" title=\"Stannis Baratheon\">Stannis Baratheon</a> at <a href=\"/index.php/Storm%27s_End\" title=\"Storm&#39;s End\">Storm's End</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok31.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok33.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok33.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Storm_of_Swords\"><i>A Storm of Swords</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Robb_Stark%27s_battle_guard&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Storm of Swords\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Red_Wedding_by_FatherStone.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/7/76/Red_Wedding_by_FatherStone.jpg/300px-Red_Wedding_by_FatherStone.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"338\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/7/76/Red_Wedding_by_FatherStone.jpg/450px-Red_Wedding_by_FatherStone.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/7/76/Red_Wedding_by_FatherStone.jpg/600px-Red_Wedding_by_FatherStone.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Red_Wedding_by_FatherStone.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>The <a href=\"/index.php/Red_Wedding\" title=\"Red Wedding\">Red Wedding</a>, by Fatherstone ©</div></div></div>\n<p>During the wedding feast of Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Edmure_Tully\" title=\"Edmure Tully\">Edmure Tully</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Roslin_Frey\" title=\"Roslin Frey\">Roslin Frey</a> at the <a href=\"/index.php/Twins\" title=\"Twins\">Twins</a>, Robb is protected by Robin, Dacey, <a href=\"/index.php/Patrek_Mallister\" title=\"Patrek Mallister\">Patrek Mallister</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/Jon_Umber_(son_of_Jon)\" title=\"Jon Umber (son of Jon)\">Smalljon Umber</a>, who all remain sober.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos51.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos51.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> When Robb is betrayed by <a href=\"/index.php/House_Frey\" title=\"House Frey\">House Frey</a> in the <a href=\"/index.php/Red_Wedding\" title=\"Red Wedding\">Red Wedding</a>, however, most of his personal guard is killed along with him.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos51.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos51.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Known_Members\">Known Members</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Robb_Stark%27s_battle_guard&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Known Members\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/Lucas_Blackwood\" title=\"Lucas Blackwood\">Lucas Blackwood</a>, slain by Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Hosteen_Frey\" title=\"Hosteen Frey\">Hosteen Frey</a> at the <a href=\"/index.php/Red_Wedding\" title=\"Red Wedding\">Red Wedding</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos51.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos51.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Robin_Flint\" title=\"Robin Flint\">Robin Flint</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot63.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot63.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> stabbed by <a href=\"/index.php/House_Frey\" title=\"House Frey\">Freys</a> at the Red Wedding.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos51.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos51.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>No less than five <a href=\"/index.php/House_Frey\" title=\"House Frey\">Freys</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot63.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot63.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/Olyvar_Frey\" title=\"Olyvar Frey\">Olyvar Frey</a>, Robb's squire, sent away from the <a href=\"/index.php/Twins\" title=\"Twins\">Twins</a> before the Red Wedding.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos51.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos51.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Perwyn_Frey\" title=\"Perwyn Frey\">Perwyn Frey</a>, sent away from the Twins before the Red Wedding.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos49.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos49.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup></li></ul></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Theon_Greyjoy\" title=\"Theon Greyjoy\">Theon Greyjoy</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot63.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot63.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> Robb's childhood friend, betrays Robb for his father, Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Balon_Greyjoy\" title=\"Balon Greyjoy\">Balon Greyjoy</a>, and leads the <a href=\"/index.php/Capture_of_Winterfell\" title=\"Capture of Winterfell\">capture of Winterfell</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok46.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_9-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok46.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Daryn_Hornwood\" title=\"Daryn Hornwood\">Daryn Hornwood</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot63.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot63.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> slain by Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Jaime_Lannister\" title=\"Jaime Lannister\">Jaime Lannister</a> in the <a href=\"/index.php/Battle_in_the_Whispering_Wood\" title=\"Battle in the Whispering Wood\">Whispering Wood</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot63.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot63.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Eddard_Karstark\" title=\"Eddard Karstark\">Eddard Karstark</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot63.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot63.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> slain by Jaime in the Whispering Wood.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot63.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-10\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot63.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Torrhen_Karstark\" title=\"Torrhen Karstark\">Torrhen Karstark</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot63.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-11\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot63.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> slain by Jaime in the Whispering Wood.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot63.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-12\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot63.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Donnel_Locke\" title=\"Donnel Locke\">Donnel Locke</a>, slain by a crossbowman at the Red Wedding.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos51.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos51.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Patrek_Mallister\" title=\"Patrek Mallister\">Patrek Mallister</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot63.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-13\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot63.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> captured at the Red Wedding.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_10-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Wendel_Manderly\" title=\"Wendel Manderly\">Wendel Manderly</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot63.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-14\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot63.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> slain by a crossbowman at the Red Wedding.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos51.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos51.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Dacey_Mormont\" title=\"Dacey Mormont\">Dacey Mormont</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot63.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-15\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot63.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> the only woman of the group, slain by Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Ryman_Frey\" title=\"Ryman Frey\">Ryman Frey</a> at the Red Wedding.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos51.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos51.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Owen_Norrey\" title=\"Owen Norrey\">Owen Norrey</a>, slain by a crossbowman at the Red Wedding.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos51.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos51.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Jon_Umber_(son_of_Jon)\" title=\"Jon Umber (son of Jon)\">Smalljon Umber</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot63.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-16\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot63.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> beheaded by <a href=\"/index.php/House_Bolton\" title=\"House Bolton\">Boltons</a> or <a href=\"/index.php/House_Karstark\" title=\"House Karstark\">Karstarks</a> at the Red Wedding.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos51.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos51.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Raynald_Westerling\" title=\"Raynald Westerling\">Raynald Westerling</a>, Robb's banner-bearer,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos45.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_11-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos45.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup> presumed dead after being shot with Frey arrows at the Red Wedding.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc44.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_12-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc44.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-12\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Robb_Stark%27s_battle_guard&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><a href=\"/index.php/Robb_Stark\" title=\"Robb Stark\">Robb</a> turned the big grey stallion and walked him slowly away from her, <a href=\"/index.php/Grey_Wind\" title=\"Grey Wind\">Grey Wind</a> shadowing his steps. Behind him his battle guard formed up. When he'd forced Catelyn to accept her protectors, she had insisted that he be guarded as well, and the <a href=\"/index.php/Bannermen\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Bannermen\">lords bannermen</a> had agreed. Many of their sons had clamored for the honor of riding with the Young Wolf, as they had taken to calling him.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot63.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-17\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot63.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Catelyn_Stark\" title=\"Catelyn Stark\">Catelyn Stark</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>I have fought beside the Young Wolf in every battle, he has not lost one yet.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos45.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_11-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos45.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Dacey_Mormont\" title=\"Dacey Mormont\">Dacey Mormont</a> to <a href=\"/index.php/Maege_Mormont\" title=\"Maege Mormont\">Maege Mormont</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>A wedding feast was not a battle, but there were always dangers when men were in their cups, and a king should never be unguarded.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos51.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-10\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos51.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Catelyn_Stark\" title=\"Catelyn Stark\">Catelyn Stark</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Robb_Stark%27s_battle_guard&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\" style=\"-webkit-column-width:200px; -moz-column-width:200px; column-width:200px; -webkit-column-count:2; -moz-column-count:2; column-count:2;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap mw-references-columns\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Ragot63.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Ragot63.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.00</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Ragot63.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1